OL,5, The calls come whenever he can get a   
OL,6, signal. Or whenever he can get enough  
OL,7, electricity to charge his phone.       
OL,9,FHe eats when he can find food. He      
OL,10,Ftravels from one scene of desolation to
OL,11,Fanother. As long as he can find petrol.
OL,13,FAnd Mahmoud Bassam worries about his   
OL,14,Fwife and 11-month-old child because    
OL,15,Fthey have to move to avoid the bombing.
OL,16,FSo when he leaves home in the morning  
OL,17,Fhe is never sure they will be in the   
OL,18,Fsame place when he gets back at night. 
